TITLE: Optimizing Attachment Updates with isAttachmentEqual - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code defines a function `isAttachmentEqual` to optimize updates of location attachments in the chat. It compares the latitude, longitude, and ended_at properties of the previous and next attachments. If all three properties are equal, it returns `true`, preventing unnecessary re-renders. This is crucial for performance, especially when dealing with frequent live location updates. This is necessary because default memoization will not trigger updates based on custom properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/getstream/stream-chat-react-native/blob/develop/docusaurus/reactnative_versioned_docs/version-5.x.x/guides/live-location-sharing.mdx#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const isAttachmentEqual: NonNullable<React.ComponentProps<typeof Channel<StreamChatGenerics>>['isAttachmentEqual']> = (
  prevAttachment,
  nextAttachment,
) => {
  if (prevAttachment.type === 'location' && nextAttachment.type === 'location') {
    return (
      prevAttachment.latitude === nextAttachment.latitude &&
      prevAttachment.longitude === nextAttachment.longitude &&
      prevAttachment.ended_at === nextAttachment.ended_at
    );
  }
  return true;
};
```

