TITLE: Handling ACTION_PRESS Event in Notifee - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet shows how to handle the `ACTION_PRESS` event from Notifee when the user presses on a notification in the background on Android. It extracts the channel ID from the notification data and navigates to the corresponding channel screen using React Navigation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/getstream/stream-chat-react-native/blob/develop/docusaurus/docs/reactnative/guides/push-notifications-v2.mdx#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
notifee.onBackgroundEvent(async ({ detail, type }) => {
  if (type === EventType.ACTION_PRESS) {
    // user press on notification detected while app was on background on Android
    const channelId = detail.notification?.data?.channel_id;
    if (channelId) {
      navigationContainerRef.current?.navigate('ChannelScreen', { channelId });
    }
    await Promise.resolve();
  }
});
```

