TITLE: Update FCM Server Key via Stream Chat Server side SDK
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to update the Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) server key and notification/data templates using the Stream Chat Server-Side SDK.  It requires the API Key and API Secret for authentication. The `firebase_config` object includes `server_key`, `notification_template`, and `data_template` for customizing push notifications.  It uses async/await syntax.
SOURCE: https://github.com/getstream/stream-chat-react-native/blob/develop/docusaurus/docs/reactnative/guides/push-notifications-v1.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const client = StreamChat.getInstance(API_KEY, API_SECRET);
await client.updateAppSettings({
  firebase_config: {
    server_key: 'server_key',
    notification_template: `{"message":{"notification":{"title":"New messages","body":"You have {{ unread_count }} new message(s) from {{ sender.name }}"},"android":{"ttl":"86400s","notification":{"click_action":"OPEN_ACTIVITY_1"}}}}`,
    data_template: `{"sender":"{{ sender.id }}","channel":{"type": "{{ channel.type }}","id":"{{ channel.id }}"},"message":"{{ message.id }}"}`,
  },
});
```

