TITLE: Preparing Static Map URL
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript function generates a URL for a static map image from the Google Maps Static API. It takes latitude and longitude as input and constructs a URL with parameters for center, zoom, size, map type, API key, and a marker.
SOURCE: https://github.com/getstream/stream-chat-react-native/blob/develop/docusaurus/reactnative_versioned_docs/version-3.x.x/guides/attachment_customizations.mdx#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const prepareStaticMapUrl = (lat, long) => {
  let baseURL = 'https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?';
  let url = new URL(baseURL);
  let params = url.searchParams;
  params.append('center', `${lat},${long}`);
  params.append('zoom', '15');
  params.append('size', '600x300');
  params.append('maptype', 'roadmap');
  params.append('key', MAPS_API_KEY);
  params.append('markers', `color:red|${lat},${long}`);

  return url.toString();
};

```

