TITLE: Replacing Infinite Scroll with Load More Button - React Native
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to replace the default infinite scroll pagination in the ChannelList component with a 'Load More' button. It defines a `FooterLoadMoreButton` component that uses the `useChannelsContext` hook to access pagination-related flags and the `loadNextPage` function. It then uses the `additionalFlatListProps` prop to override the default FlatList props, adding the 'Load More' button as the `ListFooterComponent` and disabling infinite scroll by setting `onEndReached` to null.
SOURCE: https://github.com/getstream/stream-chat-react-native/blob/develop/docusaurus/reactnative_versioned_docs/version-5.x.x/guides/custom-channel-list.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { Button } from 'react-native';
import { useChannelsContext } from 'stream-chat-react-native';

const FooterLoadMoreButton = () => {
  const { loadingChannels, loadNextPage, hasNextPage } = useChannelsContext();

  if (loadingChannels || !hasNextPage) return null;

  return <Button title={'Load More'} onPress={loadNextPage} />;
};

<ChannelList
  additionalFlatListProps={{
    ListFooterComponent: FooterLoadMoreButton,
    onEndReached: () => null,
  }}
/>;
```

