TITLE: Open Google Maps with Coordinates - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript function generates a Google Maps URL from given latitude and longitude coordinates and opens it using React Native's Linking API. It checks if the URL can be opened and logs an error if not supported.
SOURCE: https://github.com/getstream/stream-chat-react-native/blob/develop/docusaurus/reactnative_versioned_docs/version-5.x.x/guides/custom-attachment.mdx#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
const goToGoogleMaps = (lat, long) => {
  const url = `https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=${lat},${long}`;

  Linking.canOpenURL(url).then(supported => {
    if (supported) {
      Linking.openURL(url);
    } else {
      console.log(`Don't know how to open URI: ${url}`);
    }
  });
};
```

