TITLE: Metro Configuration (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet provides a `metro.config.js` configuration for React Native projects using the Stream Chat React Native SDK. It uses the `extractLinkedPackages` helper from the SDK to resolve dependency collisions. The configuration sets up resolver options to blacklist modules and specify extra node modules, along with watch folders for development.
SOURCE: https://github.com/getstream/stream-chat-react-native/blob/develop/examples/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const PATH = require('path');
const blacklist = require('metro-config/src/defaults/exclusionList');

const extractLinkedPackages = require('stream-chat-react-native-core/metro-dev-helpers/extract-linked-packages');

const projectRoot = PATH.resolve(__dirname);

const { alternateRoots, extraNodeModules, moduleBlacklist } = extractLinkedPackages(projectRoot);

module.exports = {
  resolver: {
    blacklistRE: blacklist(moduleBlacklist),
    extraNodeModules,
    useWatchman: false,
  },
  watchFolders: [projectRoot].concat(alternateRoots),
};
```

